  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Commissions Joshua'
      title: God Commissions Joshua
      number: 1
      content: "  After the death of Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses\u2019
        assistant, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CMoses my servant is dead. Now therefore arise, go over this
        Jordan, you and all this people, into the land that I am giving to them,
        to the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given
        to you, just as I promised to Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'From the wilderness and this Lebanon as far as the great river, the
        river Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites to the Great Sea toward the
        going down of the sun shall be your territory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'No man shall be able to stand before you all the days of your life.
        Just as I was with Moses, so I will be with you. I will not leave you or
        forsake you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Be strong and courageous, for you shall cause this people to inherit
        the land that I swore to their fathers to give them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Only be strong and very courageous, being careful to do according
        to all the law that Moses my servant commanded you. Do not turn from it to
        the right hand or to the left, that you may have good success[[COMMENT(0)]]
        wherever you go. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall
        meditate on it day and night, so that you may be careful to do according
        to all that is written in it. For then you will make your way prosperous,
        and then you will have good success. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Joshua Assumes Command'
      title: Joshua Assumes Command
      number: 9
      content: "Have I not commanded you? Be strong and courageous. Do not be frightened,
        and do not be dismayed, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is with
        you wherever you go.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Joshua commanded the officers of the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CPass through the midst of the camp and command the people,
        \u2018Prepare your provisions, for within three days you are to pass over
        this Jordan to go in to take possession of the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving you to possess.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        Joshua said, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CRemember the word that Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded you, saying, \u2018The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God is
        providing you a place of rest and will give you this land.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in
        the land that Moses gave you beyond the Jordan, but all the men of valor
        among you shall pass over armed before your brothers and shall help them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gives rest to your brothers
        as he has to you, and they also take possession of the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God is giving them. Then you shall return to the land of your possession
        and shall possess it, the land that Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave you beyond the Jordan toward the sunrise.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And they answered Joshua, \u201CAll that you have commanded us we
        will do, and wherever you send us we will go. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Just as we obeyed Moses in all things, so we will obey you. Only
        may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God be with you, as he was with
        Moses! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Whoever rebels against your commandment and disobeys your words,
        whatever you command him, shall be put to death. Only be strong and courageous.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rahab Hides the Spies'
      title: Rahab Hides the Spies
      number: 1
      content: "  And Joshua the son of Nun sent[[COMMENT(0)]] two men secretly from
        Shittim as spies, saying, \u201CGo, view the land, especially Jericho.\u201D
        And they went and came into the house of a prostitute whose name was Rahab
        and lodged there. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:1 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And it was told to the king of Jericho, \u201CBehold, men of Israel
        have come here tonight to search out the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the king of Jericho sent to Rahab, saying, \u201CBring out the
        men who have come to you, who entered your house, for they have come to search
        out all the land.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But the woman had taken the two men and hidden them. And she said,
        \u201CTrue, the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when the gate was about to be closed at dark, the men went out.
        I do not know where the men went. Pursue them quickly, for you will overtake
        them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But she had brought them up to the roof and hid them with the stalks
        of flax that she had laid in order on the roof. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So the men pursued after them on the way to the Jordan as far as
        the fords. And the gate was shut as soon as the pursuers had gone out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Before the men[[COMMENT(0)]] lay down, she came up to them on the
        roof '
      comments:
      - number: '2:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "and said to the men, \u201CI know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given you the land, and that the fear of you has fallen upon us, and
        that all the inhabitants of the land melt away before you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For we have heard how the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  dried up the
        water of the Red Sea before you when you came out of Egypt, and what you
        did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan, to Sihon
        and Og, whom you devoted to destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as soon as we heard it, our hearts melted, and there was no spirit
        left in any man because of you, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God, he is God in the heavens above and on the earth beneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now then, please swear to me by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that,
        as I have dealt kindly with you, you also will deal kindly with my father\u2019s
        house, and give me a sure sign "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "that you will save alive my father and mother, my brothers and sisters,
        and all who belong to them, and deliver our lives from death.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And the men said to her, \u201COur life for yours even to death!
        If you do not tell this business of ours, then when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gives us the land we will deal kindly and faithfully with you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house
        was built into the city wall, so that she lived in the wall. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And she said[[COMMENT(0)]] to them, \u201CGo into the hills, or the
        pursuers will encounter you, and hide there three days until the pursuers
        have returned. Then afterward you may go your way.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The men said to her, \u201CWe will be guiltless with respect to this
        oath of yours that you have made us swear. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Behold, when we come into the land, you shall tie this scarlet cord
        in the window through which you let us down, and you shall gather into your
        house your father and mother, your brothers, and all your father\u2019s household. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then if anyone goes out of the doors of your house into the street,
        his blood shall be on his own head, and we shall be guiltless. But if a hand
        is laid on anyone who is with you in the house, his blood shall be on our
        head. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "But if you tell this business of ours, then we shall be guiltless
        with respect to your oath that you have made us swear.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And she said, \u201CAccording to your words, so be it.\u201D Then
        she sent them away, and they departed. And she tied the scarlet cord in the
        window.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They departed and went into the hills and remained there three days
        until the pursuers returned, and the pursuers searched all along the way
        and found nothing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the two men returned. They came down from the hills and passed
        over and came to Joshua the son of Nun, and they told him all that had happened
        to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And they said to Joshua, \u201CTruly the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given all the land into our hands. And also, all the inhabitants of the
        land melt away because of us.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Crosses the Jordan'
      title: Israel Crosses the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Joshua rose early in the morning and they set out from Shittim.
        And they came to the Jordan, he and all the people of Israel, and lodged
        there before they passed over. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'At the end of three days the officers went through the camp '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and commanded the people, \u201CAs soon as you see the ark of the
        covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God being carried by the
        Levitical priests, then you shall set out from your place and follow it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Yet there shall be a distance between you and it, about 2,000 cubits[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in length. Do not come near it, in order that you may know the way you shall
        go, for you have not passed this way before.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '3:4 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Joshua said to the people, \u201CConsecrate yourselves, for
        tomorrow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do wonders among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Joshua said to the priests, \u201CTake up the ark of the covenant
        and pass on before the people.\u201D So they took up the ark of the covenant
        and went before the people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CToday I will
        begin to exalt you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that, as
        I was with Moses, so I will be with you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And as for you, command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant,
        \u2018When you come to the brink of the waters of the Jordan, you shall stand
        still in the Jordan.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Joshua said to the people of Israel, \u201CCome here and listen
        to the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CHere is how you shall know that the living
        God is among you and that he will without fail drive out from before you
        the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Hivites, the Perizzites, the Girgashites,
        the Amorites, and the Jebusites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Behold, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        is passing over before you into the Jordan. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:11 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now therefore take twelve men from the tribes of Israel, from each
        tribe a man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when the soles of the feet of the priests bearing the ark of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the Lord of all the earth, shall rest in
        the waters of the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan shall be cut off from
        flowing, and the waters coming down from above shall stand in one heap.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So when the people set out from their tents to pass over the Jordan
        with the priests bearing the ark of the covenant before the people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and as soon as those bearing the ark had come as far as the Jordan,
        and the feet of the priests bearing the ark were dipped in the brink of the
        water (now the Jordan overflows all its banks throughout the time of harvest), '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the waters coming down from above stood and rose up in a heap very
        far away, at Adam, the city that is beside Zarethan, and those flowing down
        toward the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, were completely cut off. And
        the people passed over opposite Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Now the priests bearing the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        stood firmly on dry ground in the midst of the Jordan, and all Israel was
        passing over on dry ground until all the nation finished passing over the
        Jordan.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Twelve Memorial Stones from the Jordan'
      title: Twelve Memorial Stones from the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: '  When all the nation had finished passing over the Jordan, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CTake twelve men from the people, from each tribe a man, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and command them, saying, \u2018Take twelve stones from here out
        of the midst of the Jordan, from the very place where the priests\u2019 feet
        stood firmly, and bring them over with you and lay them down in the place
        where you lodge tonight.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then Joshua called the twelve men from the people of Israel, whom
        he had appointed, a man from each tribe. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CPass on before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God into the midst of the Jordan, and take up each of you a stone upon
        his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the people of Israel, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "that this may be a sign among you. When your children ask in time
        to come, \u2018What do those stones mean to you?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "then you shall tell them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off
        before the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. When it
        passed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. So these stones
        shall be to the people of Israel a memorial forever.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the people of Israel did just as Joshua commanded and took up
        twelve stones out of the midst of the Jordan, according to the number of
        the tribes of the people of Israel, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        told Joshua. And they carried them over with them to the place where they
        lodged and laid them down[[COMMENT(0)]] there. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:8 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joshua set up[[COMMENT(0)]] twelve stones in the midst of the
        Jordan, in the place where the feet of the priests bearing the ark of the
        covenant had stood; and they are there to this day. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:9 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the priests bearing the ark stood in the midst of the Jordan
        until everything was finished that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded
        Joshua to tell the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua.The
        people passed over in haste. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And when all the people had finished passing over, the ark of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the priests passed over before the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The sons of Reuben and the sons of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh
        passed over armed before the people of Israel, as Moses had told them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'About 40,000 ready for war passed over before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for battle, to the plains of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'On that day the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  exalted Joshua in the
        sight of all Israel, and they stood in awe of him just as they had stood
        in awe of Moses, all the days of his life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CCommand the priests bearing the ark of the testimony to come
        up out of the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Joshua commanded the priests, \u201CCome up out of the Jordan.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when the priests bearing the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came up from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests\u2019
        feet were lifted up on dry ground, the waters of the Jordan returned to their
        place and overflowed all its banks, as before.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The people came up out of the Jordan on the tenth day of the first
        month, and they encamped at Gilgal on the east border of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And those twelve stones, which they took out of the Jordan, Joshua
        set up at Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he said to the people of Israel, \u201CWhen your children ask
        their fathers in times to come, \u2018What do these stones mean?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "then you shall let your children know, \u2018Israel passed over this
        Jordan on dry ground.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God dried up the waters
        of the Jordan for you until you passed over, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God did to the Red Sea, which he dried up for us until we passed over, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "so that all the peoples of the earth may know that the hand of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is mighty, that you may fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God forever.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]"
      comments:
      - number: '4:24 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The New Generation Circumcised'
      title: The New Generation Circumcised
      number: 1
      content: '  As soon as all the kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan
        to the west, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the sea, heard
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had dried up the waters of the Jordan
        for the people of Israel until they had crossed over, their hearts melted
        and there was no longer any spirit in them because of the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "At that time the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CMake
        flint knives and circumcise the sons of Israel a second time.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua made flint knives and circumcised the sons of Israel at
        Gibeath-haaraloth.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: 'means '
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And this is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: all the males
        of the people who came out of Egypt, all the men of war, had died in the
        wilderness on the way after they had come out of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Though all the people who came out had been circumcised, yet all
        the people who were born on the way in the wilderness after they had come
        out of Egypt had not been circumcised. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the people of Israel walked forty years in the wilderness, until
        all the nation, the men of war who came out of Egypt, perished, because they
        did not obey the voice of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        swore to them that he would not let them see the land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had sworn to their fathers to give to us, a land flowing with milk and honey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So it was their children, whom he raised up in their place, that
        Joshua circumcised. For they were uncircumcised, because they had not been
        circumcised on the way.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'When the circumcising of the whole nation was finished, they remained
        in their places in the camp until they were healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: First Passover in Canaan'
      title: First Passover in Canaan
      number: 9
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CToday I
        have rolled away the reproach of Egypt from you.\u201D And so the name of
        that place is called Gilgal[[COMMENT(0)]] to this day.  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:9 '
        content: 'sounds like the Hebrew for '
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'While the people of Israel were encamped at Gilgal, they kept the
        Passover on the fourteenth day of the month in the evening on the plains
        of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the day after the Passover, on that very day, they ate of the
        produce of the land, unleavened cakes and parched grain. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The Commander of the \u2019s Army"
      title: "The Commander of the \u2019s Army"
      number: 12
      content: 'And the manna ceased the day after they ate of the produce of the
        land. And there was no longer manna for the people of Israel, but they ate
        of the fruit of the land of Canaan that year.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Joshua was by Jericho, he lifted up his eyes and looked, and
        behold, a man was standing before him with his drawn sword in his hand. And
        Joshua went to him and said to him, \u201CAre you for us, or for our adversaries?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he said, \u201CNo; but I am the commander of the army of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Now I have come.\u201D And Joshua fell on his
        face to the earth and worshiped[[COMMENT(0)]] and said to him, \u201CWhat
        does my lord say to his servant?\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '5:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the commander of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s army
        said to Joshua, \u201CTake off your sandals from your feet, for the place
        where you are standing is holy.\u201D And Joshua did so."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Jericho'
      title: The Fall of Jericho
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Jericho was shut up inside and outside because of the people
        of Israel. None went out, and none came in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CSee, I
        have given Jericho into your hand, with its king and mighty men of valor. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You shall march around the city, all the men of war going around
        the city once. Thus shall you do for six days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Seven priests shall bear seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before
        the ark. On the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times,
        and the priests shall blow the trumpets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And when they make a long blast with the ram\u2019s horn, when you
        hear the sound of the trumpet, then all the people shall shout with a great
        shout, and the wall of the city will fall down flat,[[COMMENT(0)]] and the
        people shall go up, everyone straight before him.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 20
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So Joshua the son of Nun called the priests and said to them, \u201CTake
        up the ark of the covenant and let seven priests bear seven trumpets of rams\u2019
        horns before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And he said to the people, \u201CGo forward. March around the city
        and let the armed men pass on before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And just as Joshua had commanded the people, the seven priests bearing
        the seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        went forward, blowing the trumpets, with the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        following them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The armed men were walking before the priests who were blowing the
        trumpets, and the rear guard was walking after the ark, while the trumpets
        blew continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "But Joshua commanded the people, \u201CYou shall not shout or make
        your voice heard, neither shall any word go out of your mouth, until the
        day I tell you to shout. Then you shall shout.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So he caused the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to circle
        the city, going about it once. And they came into the camp and spent the
        night in the camp.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Joshua rose early in the morning, and the priests took up the
        ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the seven priests bearing the seven trumpets of rams\u2019 horns
        before the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> walked on, and they blew
        the trumpets continually. And the armed men were walking before them, and
        the rear guard was walking after the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        while the trumpets blew continually. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the second day they marched around the city once, and returned
        into the camp. So they did for six days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'On the seventh day they rose early, at the dawn of day, and marched
        around the city in the same manner seven times. It was only on that day that
        they marched around the city seven times. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And at the seventh time, when the priests had blown the trumpets,
        Joshua said to the people, \u201CShout, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has given you the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the city and all that is within it shall be devoted to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        for destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]] Only Rahab the prostitute and all who are
        with her in her house shall live, because she hid the messengers whom we
        sent. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:17 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          also verses 18, 21
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But you, keep yourselves from the things devoted to destruction,
        lest when you have devoted them you take any of the devoted things and make
        the camp of Israel a thing for destruction and bring trouble upon it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all silver and gold, and every vessel of bronze and iron, are
        holy to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; they shall go into the treasury
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So the people shouted, and the trumpets were blown. As soon as the
        people heard the sound of the trumpet, the people shouted a great shout,
        and the wall fell down flat, so that the people went up into the city, every
        man straight before him, and they captured the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then they devoted all in the city to destruction, both men and women,
        young and old, oxen, sheep, and donkeys, with the edge of the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But to the two men who had spied out the land, Joshua said, \u201CGo
        into the prostitute\u2019s house and bring out from there the woman and all
        who belong to her, as you swore to her.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So the young men who had been spies went in and brought out Rahab
        and her father and mother and brothers and all who belonged to her. And they
        brought all her relatives and put them outside the camp of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And they burned the city with fire, and everything in it. Only the
        silver and gold, and the vessels of bronze and of iron, they put into the
        treasury of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "But Rahab the prostitute and her father\u2019s household and all
        who belonged to her, Joshua saved alive. And she has lived in Israel to this
        day, because she hid the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Joshua laid an oath on them at that time, saying, \u201CCursed before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> be the man who rises up and rebuilds this
        city, Jericho.\u201CAt the cost of his firstborn shall helay its foundation,and
        at the cost of his youngest sonshall he set up its gates.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was with Joshua, and his fame
        was in all the land.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Defeated at Ai'
      title: Israel Defeated at Ai
      number: 1
      content: '  But the people of Israel broke faith in regard to the devoted things,
        for Achan the son of Carmi, son of Zabdi, son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah,
        took some of the devoted things. And the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        burned against the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is near Beth-aven, east
        of Bethel, and said to them, \u201CGo up and spy out the land.\u201D And
        the men went up and spied out Ai. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they returned to Joshua and said to him, \u201CDo not have all
        the people go up, but let about two or three thousand men go up and attack
        Ai. Do not make the whole people toil up there, for they are few.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So about three thousand men went up there from the people. And they
        fled before the men of Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the men of Ai killed about thirty-six of their men and chased
        them before the gate as far as Shebarim and struck them at the descent. And
        the hearts of the people melted and became as water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then Joshua tore his clothes and fell to the earth on his face before
        the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> until the evening, he and the
        elders of Israel. And they put dust on their heads. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CAlas, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>, why
        have you brought this people over the Jordan at all, to give us into the
        hands of the Amorites, to destroy us? Would that we had been content to dwell
        beyond the Jordan! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Lord, what can I say, when Israel has turned their backs before
        their enemies! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Sin of Achan'
      title: The Sin of Achan
      number: 9
      content: "For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear
        of it and will surround us and cut off our name from the earth. And what
        will you do for your great name?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CGet up! Why
        have you fallen on your face? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Israel has sinned; they have transgressed my covenant that I commanded
        them; they have taken some of the devoted things; they have stolen and lied
        and put them among their own belongings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore the people of Israel cannot stand before their enemies.
        They turn their backs before their enemies, because they have become devoted
        for destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]] I will be with you no more, unless you destroy
        the devoted things from among you. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:12 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Get up! Consecrate the people and say, \u2018Consecrate yourselves
        for tomorrow; for thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Israel,
        \u201CThere are devoted things in your midst, O Israel. You cannot stand
        before your enemies until you take away the devoted things from among you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In the morning therefore you shall be brought near by your tribes.
        And the tribe that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes by lot shall come
        near by clans. And the clan that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> takes shall
        come near by households. And the household that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        takes shall come near man by man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he who is taken with the devoted things shall be burned with
        fire, he and all that he has, because he has transgressed the covenant of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and because he has done an outrageous thing
        in Israel.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua rose early in the morning and brought Israel near tribe
        by tribe, and the tribe of Judah was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he brought near the clans of Judah, and the clan of the Zerahites
        was taken. And he brought near the clan of the Zerahites man by man, and
        Zabdi was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And he brought near his household man by man, and Achan the son of
        Carmi, son of Zabdi, son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Then Joshua said to Achan, \u201CMy son, give glory to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Israel and give praise[[COMMENT(0)]] to him. And tell me now what
        you have done; do not hide it from me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '7:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And Achan answered Joshua, \u201CTruly I have sinned against the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel, and this is what I did: "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "when I saw among the spoil a beautiful cloak from Shinar, and 200
        shekels of silver, and a bar of gold weighing 50 shekels,[[COMMENT(0)]] then
        I coveted them and took them. And see, they are hidden in the earth inside
        my tent, with the silver underneath.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '7:21 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and behold,
        it was hidden in his tent with the silver underneath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they took them out of the tent and brought them to Joshua and
        to all the people of Israel. And they laid them down before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel with him took Achan the son of Zerah, and
        the silver and the cloak and the bar of gold, and his sons and daughters
        and his oxen and donkeys and sheep and his tent and all that he had. And
        they brought them up to the Valley of Achor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CWhy did you bring trouble on us? The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        brings trouble on you today.\u201D And all Israel stoned him with stones.
        They burned them with fire and stoned them with stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: And they raised over him a great heap of stones that remains to this
        day. Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> turned from his burning anger.
        Therefore, to this day the name of that place is called the Valley of Achor.[[COMMENT(0)]]
      comments:
      - number: '7:26 '
        content: 'means '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Ai'
      title: The Fall of Ai
      number: 1
      content: "  And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CDo not
        fear and do not be dismayed. Take all the fighting men with you, and arise,
        go up to Ai. See, I have given into your hand the king of Ai, and his people,
        his city, and his land. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And you shall do to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho and its
        king. Only its spoil and its livestock you shall take as plunder for yourselves.
        Lay an ambush against the city, behind it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Joshua and all the fighting men arose to go up to Ai. And Joshua
        chose 30,000 mighty men of valor and sent them out by night. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he commanded them, \u201CBehold, you shall lie in ambush against
        the city, behind it. Do not go very far from the city, but all of you remain
        ready. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I and all the people who are with me will approach the city.
        And when they come out against us just as before, we shall flee before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they will come out after us, until we have drawn them away from
        the city. For they will say, \u2018They are fleeing from us, just as before.\u2019
        So we will flee before them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then you shall rise up from the ambush and seize the city, for the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will give it into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And as soon as you have taken the city, you shall set the city on
        fire. You shall do according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        See, I have commanded you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua sent them out. And they went to the place of ambush and
        lay between Bethel and Ai, to the west of Ai, but Joshua spent that night
        among the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Joshua arose early in the morning and mustered the people and went
        up, he and the elders of Israel, before the people to Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And all the fighting men who were with him went up and drew near
        before the city and encamped on the north side of Ai, with a ravine between
        them and Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He took about 5,000 men and set them in ambush between Bethel and
        Ai, to the west of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So they stationed the forces, the main encampment that was north
        of the city and its rear guard west of the city. But Joshua spent that night
        in the valley. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And as soon as the king of Ai saw this, he and all his people, the
        men of the city, hurried and went out early to the appointed place[[COMMENT(0)]]
        toward the Arabah to meet Israel in battle. But he did not know that there
        was an ambush against him behind the city. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:14 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joshua and all Israel pretended to be beaten before them and
        fled in the direction of the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So all the people who were in the city were called together to pursue
        them, and as they pursued Joshua they were drawn away from the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Not a man was left in Ai or Bethel who did not go out after Israel.
        They left the city open and pursued Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CStretch
        out the javelin that is in your hand toward Ai, for I will give it into your
        hand.\u201D And Joshua stretched out the javelin that was in his hand toward
        the city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And the men in the ambush rose quickly out of their place, and as
        soon as he had stretched out his hand, they ran and entered the city and
        captured it. And they hurried to set the city on fire. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So when the men of Ai looked back, behold, the smoke of the city
        went up to heaven, and they had no power to flee this way or that, for the
        people who fled to the wilderness turned back against the pursuers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had captured the
        city, and that the smoke of the city went up, then they turned back and struck
        down the men of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the others came out from the city against them, so they were
        in the midst of Israel, some on this side, and some on that side. And Israel
        struck them down, until there was left none that survived or escaped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'But the king of Ai they took alive, and brought him near to Joshua.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'When Israel had finished killing all the inhabitants of Ai in the
        open wilderness where they pursued them, and all of them to the very last
        had fallen by the edge of the sword, all Israel returned to Ai and struck
        it down with the edge of the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And all who fell that day, both men and women, were 12,000, all the
        people of Ai. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But Joshua did not draw back his hand with which he stretched out
        the javelin until he had devoted all the inhabitants of Ai to destruction.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:26 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as their
        plunder, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he
        commanded Joshua. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joshua burned Ai and made it forever a heap of ruins, as it is
        to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: Joshua Renews the Covenant'
      title: Joshua Renews the Covenant
      number: 29
      content: 'And he hanged the king of Ai on a tree until evening. And at sunset
        Joshua commanded, and they took his body down from the tree and threw it
        at the entrance of the gate of the city and raised over it a great heap of
        stones, which stands there to this day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'At that time Joshua built an altar to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, on Mount Ebal, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "just as Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        commanded the people of Israel, as it is written in the Book of the Law of
        Moses, \u201Can altar of uncut stones, upon which no man has wielded an iron
        tool.\u201D And they offered on it burnt offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and sacrificed peace offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And there, in the presence of the people of Israel, he wrote on the
        stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he had written. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And all Israel, sojourner as well as native born, with their elders
        and officers and their judges, stood on opposite sides of the ark before
        the Levitical priests who carried the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        half of them in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front of Mount
        Ebal, just as Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded
        at the first, to bless the people of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'And afterward he read all the words of the law, the blessing and
        the curse, according to all that is written in the Book of the Law. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: There was not a word of all that Moses commanded that Joshua did not
        read before all the assembly of Israel, and the women, and the little ones,
        and the sojourners who lived[[COMMENT(0)]] among them.
      comments:
      - number: '8:35 '
        content: 'Or '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Gibeonite Deception'
      title: The Gibeonite Deception
      number: 1
      content: '  As soon as all the kings who were beyond the Jordan in the hill
        country and in the lowland all along the coast of the Great Sea toward Lebanon,
        the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites,
        and the Jebusites, heard of this, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'they gathered together as one to fight against Joshua and Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But when the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Joshua had done to
        Jericho and to Ai, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'they on their part acted with cunning and went and made ready provisions
        and took worn-out sacks for their donkeys, and wineskins, worn-out and torn
        and mended, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'with worn-out, patched sandals on their feet, and worn-out clothes.
        And all their provisions were dry and crumbly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And they went to Joshua in the camp at Gilgal and said to him and
        to the men of Israel, \u201CWe have come from a distant country, so now make
        a covenant with us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But the men of Israel said to the Hivites, \u201CPerhaps you live
        among us; then how can we make a covenant with you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "They said to Joshua, \u201CWe are your servants.\u201D And Joshua
        said to them, \u201CWho are you? And where do you come from?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "They said to him, \u201CFrom a very distant country your servants
        have come, because of the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God.
        For we have heard a report of him, and all that he did in Egypt, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and all that he did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond
        the Jordan, to Sihon the king of Heshbon, and to Og king of Bashan, who lived
        in Ashtaroth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So our elders and all the inhabitants of our country said to us,
        \u2018Take provisions in your hand for the journey and go to meet them and
        say to them, \u201CWe are your servants. Come now, make a covenant with us.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Here is our bread. It was still warm when we took it from our houses
        as our food for the journey on the day we set out to come to you, but now,
        behold, it is dry and crumbly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "These wineskins were new when we filled them, and behold, they have
        burst. And these garments and sandals of ours are worn out from the very
        long journey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the men took some of their provisions, but did not ask counsel
        from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Joshua made peace with them and made a covenant with them, to
        let them live, and the leaders of the congregation swore to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At the end of three days after they had made a covenant with them,
        they heard that they were their neighbors and that they lived among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the people of Israel set out and reached their cities on the
        third day. Now their cities were Gibeon, Chephirah, Beeroth, and Kiriath-jearim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But the people of Israel did not attack them, because the leaders
        of the congregation had sworn to them by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel. Then all the congregation murmured against the leaders. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But all the leaders said to all the congregation, \u201CWe have sworn
        to them by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, and now we
        may not touch them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "This we will do to them: let them live, lest wrath be upon us, because
        of the oath that we swore to them.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the leaders said to them, \u201CLet them live.\u201D So they
        became cutters of wood and drawers of water for all the congregation, just
        as the leaders had said of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Joshua summoned them, and he said to them, \u201CWhy did you deceive
        us, saying, \u2018We are very far from you,\u2019 when you dwell among us? "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore you are cursed, and some of you shall never be anything
        but servants, cutters of wood and drawers of water for the house of my God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "They answered Joshua, \u201CBecause it was told to your servants
        for a certainty that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God had commanded
        his servant Moses to give you all the land and to destroy all the inhabitants
        of the land from before you\u2014so we feared greatly for our lives because
        of you and did this thing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And now, behold, we are in your hand. Whatever seems good and right
        in your sight to do to us, do it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So he did this to them and delivered them out of the hand of the
        people of Israel, and they did not kill them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: But Joshua made them that day cutters of wood and drawers of water
        for the congregation and for the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        to this day, in the place that he should choose.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Sun Stands Still'
      title: The Sun Stands Still
      number: 1
      content: '  As soon as Adoni-zedek, king of Jerusalem, heard how Joshua had
        captured Ai and had devoted it to destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]]  doing to Ai
        and its king as he had done to Jericho and its king, and how the inhabitants
        of Gibeon had made peace with Israel and were among them, '
      comments:
      - number: '10:1 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction);
          also verses 28, 35, 37, 39, 40
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'he[[COMMENT(0)]] feared greatly, because Gibeon was a great city,
        like one of the royal cities, and because it was greater than Ai, and all
        its men were warriors. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:2 '
        content: 'One Hebrew manuscript, Vulgate (compare Syriac); most Hebrew manuscripts '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So Adoni-zedek king of Jerusalem sent to Hoham king of Hebron, to
        Piram king of Jarmuth, to Japhia king of Lachish, and to Debir king of Eglon,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CCome up to me and help me, and let us strike Gibeon. For it
        has made peace with Joshua and with the people of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the king
        of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon,
        gathered their forces and went up with all their armies and encamped against
        Gibeon and made war against it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the men of Gibeon sent to Joshua at the camp in Gilgal, saying,
        \u201CDo not relax your hand from your servants. Come up to us quickly and
        save us and help us, for all the kings of the Amorites who dwell in the hill
        country are gathered against us.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua went up from Gilgal, he and all the people of war with
        him, and all the mighty men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CDo not
        fear them, for I have given them into your hands. Not a man of them shall
        stand before you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Joshua came upon them suddenly, having marched up all night from
        Gilgal. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> threw them into a panic before
        Israel, who[[COMMENT(0)]] struck them with a great blow at Gibeon and chased
        them by the way of the ascent of Beth-horon and struck them as far as Azekah
        and Makkedah. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And as they fled before Israel, while they were going down the ascent
        of Beth-horon, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> threw down large stones from
        heaven on them as far as Azekah, and they died. There were more who died
        because of the hailstones than the sons of Israel killed with the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "At that time Joshua spoke to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in the
        day when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave the Amorites over to the sons
        of Israel, and he said in the sight of Israel,  \u201CSun, stand still at
        Gibeon,and moon, in the Valley of Aijalon.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the sun stood still, and the moon stopped,until the nation took
        vengeance on their enemies.Is this not written in the Book of Jashar? The
        sun stopped in the midst of heaven and did not hurry to set for about a whole
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'There has been no day like it before or since, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        heeded the voice of a man, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> fought for
        Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Five Amorite Kings Executed'
      title: Five Amorite Kings Executed
      number: 15
      content: 'So Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'These five kings fled and hid themselves in the cave at Makkedah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And it was told to Joshua, \u201CThe five kings have been found,
        hidden in the cave at Makkedah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joshua said, \u201CRoll large stones against the mouth of the
        cave and set men by it to guard them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "but do not stay there yourselves. Pursue your enemies; attack their
        rear guard. Do not let them enter their cities, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God has given them into your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'When Joshua and the sons of Israel had finished striking them with
        a great blow until they were wiped out, and when the remnant that remained
        of them had entered into the fortified cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'then all the people returned safe to Joshua in the camp at Makkedah.
        Not a man moved his tongue against any of the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua said, \u201COpen the mouth of the cave and bring those
        five kings out to me from the cave.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And they did so, and brought those five kings out to him from the
        cave, the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the
        king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And when they brought those kings out to Joshua, Joshua summoned
        all the men of Israel and said to the chiefs of the men of war who had gone
        with him, \u201CCome near; put your feet on the necks of these kings.\u201D
        Then they came near and put their feet on their necks. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CDo not be afraid or dismayed; be strong
        and courageous. For thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will do to all your
        enemies against whom you fight.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And afterward Joshua struck them and put them to death, and he hanged
        them on five trees. And they hung on the trees until evening. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'But at the time of the going down of the sun, Joshua commanded, and
        they took them down from the trees and threw them into the cave where they
        had hidden themselves, and they set large stones against the mouth of the
        cave, which remain to this very day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Conquest of Southern Canaan'
      title: Conquest of Southern Canaan
      number: 28
      content: 'As for Makkedah, Joshua captured it on that day and struck it, and
        its king, with the edge of the sword. He devoted to destruction every person
        in it; he left none remaining. And he did to the king of Makkedah just as
        he had done to the king of Jericho.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Makkedah to Libnah
        and fought against Libnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave it also and its king into
        the hand of Israel. And he struck it with the edge of the sword, and every
        person in it; he left none remaining in it. And he did to its king as he
        had done to the king of Jericho.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Libnah to Lachish
        and laid siege to it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Lachish into the hand of
        Israel, and he captured it on the second day and struck it with the edge
        of the sword, and every person in it, as he had done to Libnah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Then Horam king of Gezer came up to help Lachish. And Joshua struck
        him and his people, until he left none remaining.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him passed on from Lachish to Eglon.
        And they laid siege to it and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And they captured it on that day, and struck it with the edge of
        the sword. And he devoted every person in it to destruction that day, as
        he had done to Lachish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him went up from Eglon to Hebron.
        And they fought against it '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'and captured it and struck it with the edge of the sword, and its
        king and its towns, and every person in it. He left none remaining, as he
        had done to Eglon, and devoted it to destruction and every person in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then Joshua and all Israel with him turned back to Debir and fought
        against it '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'and he captured it with its king and all its towns. And they struck
        them with the edge of the sword and devoted to destruction every person in
        it; he left none remaining. Just as he had done to Hebron and to Libnah and
        its king, so he did to Debir and to its king.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'So Joshua struck the whole land, the hill country and the Negeb and
        the lowland and the slopes, and all their kings. He left none remaining,
        but devoted to destruction all that breathed, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Israel commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And Joshua struck them from Kadesh-barnea as far as Gaza, and all
        the country of Goshen, as far as Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And Joshua captured all these kings and their land at one time, because
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel fought for Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Conquests in Northern Canaan'
      title: Conquests in Northern Canaan
      number: 1
      content: '  When Jabin, king of Hazor, heard of this, he sent to Jobab king
        of Madon, and to the king of Shimron, and to the king of Achshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and to the kings who were in the northern hill country, and in the
        Arabah south of Chinneroth, and in the lowland, and in Naphoth-dor on the
        west, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'to the Canaanites in the east and the west, the Amorites, the Hittites,
        the Perizzites, and the Jebusites in the hill country, and the Hivites under
        Hermon in the land of Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they came out with all their troops, a great horde, in number
        like the sand that is on the seashore, with very many horses and chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And all these kings joined their forces and came and encamped together
        at the waters of Merom to fight against Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, \u201CDo not
        be afraid of them, for tomorrow at this time I will give over all of them,
        slain, to Israel. You shall hamstring their horses and burn their chariots
        with fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So Joshua and all his warriors came suddenly against them by the
        waters of Merom and fell upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them into the hand of Israel,
        who struck them and chased them as far as Great Sidon and Misrephoth-maim,
        and eastward as far as the Valley of Mizpeh. And they struck them until he
        left none remaining. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Joshua did to them just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said
        to him: he hamstrung their horses and burned their chariots with fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And Joshua turned back at that time and captured Hazor and struck
        its king with the sword, for Hazor formerly was the head of all those kingdoms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they struck with the sword all who were in it, devoting them
        to destruction;[[COMMENT(0)]]  there was none left that breathed. And he
        burned Hazor with fire. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:11 '
        content: That is, setting apart (devoting) as an offering to the Lord (for
          destruction); also verses 12, 20, 21
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And all the cities of those kings, and all their kings, Joshua captured,
        and struck them with the edge of the sword, devoting them to destruction,
        just as Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But none of the cities that stood on mounds did Israel burn, except
        Hazor alone; that Joshua burned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And all the spoil of these cities and the livestock, the people of
        Israel took for their plunder. But every person they struck with the edge
        of the sword until they had destroyed them, and they did not leave any who
        breathed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses his servant,
        so Moses commanded Joshua, and so Joshua did. He left nothing undone of all
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Joshua took all that land, the hill country and all the Negeb
        and all the land of Goshen and the lowland and the Arabah and the hill country
        of Israel and its lowland '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'from Mount Halak, which rises toward Seir, as far as Baal-gad in
        the Valley of Lebanon below Mount Hermon. And he captured all their kings
        and struck them and put them to death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Joshua made war a long time with all those kings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'There was not a city that made peace with the people of Israel except
        the Hivites, the inhabitants of Gibeon. They took them all in battle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For it was the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s doing to harden
        their hearts that they should come against Israel in battle, in order that
        they should be devoted to destruction and should receive no mercy but be
        destroyed, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded Moses.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Joshua came at that time and cut off the Anakim from the hill
        country, from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, and from all the hill country
        of Judah, and from all the hill country of Israel. Joshua devoted them to
        destruction with their cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'There was none of the Anakim left in the land of the people of Israel.
        Only in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod did some remain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: So Joshua took the whole land, according to all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had spoken to Moses. And Joshua gave it for an inheritance to Israel according
        to their tribal allotments. And the land had rest from war.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Kings Defeated by Moses'
      title: Kings Defeated by Moses
      number: 1
      content: '  Now these are the kings of the land whom the people of Israel defeated
        and took possession of their land beyond the Jordan toward the sunrise, from
        the Valley of the Arnon to Mount Hermon, with all the Arabah eastward: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Sihon king of the Amorites who lived at Heshbon and ruled from Aroer,
        which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and from the middle of the
        valley as far as the river Jabbok, the boundary of the Ammonites, that is,
        half of Gilead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and the Arabah to the Sea of Chinneroth eastward, and in the direction
        of Beth-jeshimoth, to the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, southward to the
        foot of the slopes of Pisgah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and Og[[COMMENT(0)]] king of Bashan, one of the remnant of the Rephaim,
        who lived at Ashtaroth and at Edrei '
      comments:
      - number: '12:4 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and ruled over Mount Hermon and Salecah and all Bashan to the boundary
        of the Geshurites and the Maacathites, and over half of Gilead to the boundary
        of Sihon king of Heshbon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: Kings Defeated by Joshua'
      title: Kings Defeated by Joshua
      number: 6
      content: 'Moses, the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the people
        of Israel defeated them. And Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        gave their land for a possession to the Reubenites and the Gadites and the
        half-tribe of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And these are the kings of the land whom Joshua and the people of
        Israel defeated on the west side of the Jordan, from Baal-gad in the Valley
        of Lebanon to Mount Halak, that rises toward Seir (and Joshua gave their
        land to the tribes of Israel as a possession according to their allotments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'in the hill country, in the lowland, in the Arabah, in the slopes,
        in the wilderness, and in the Negeb, the land of the Hittites, the Amorites,
        the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites): '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'the king of Jericho, one; the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel,
        one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of Hebron, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'the king of Jarmuth, one; the king of Lachish, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the king of Eglon, one; the king of Gezer, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'the king of Makkedah, one; the king of Bethel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'the king of Madon, one; the king of Hazor, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the king of Shimron-meron, one; the king of Achshaph, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'the king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one; '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'the king of Dor in Naphath-dor, one; the king of Goiim in Galilee,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        one; '
      comments:
      - number: '12:23 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'the king of Tirzah, one: in all, thirty-one kings.'
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Land Still to Be Conquered'
      title: Land Still to Be Conquered
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Joshua was old and advanced in years, and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to him, \u201CYou are old and advanced in years, and there remains yet
        very much land to possess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'This is the land that yet remains: all the regions of the Philistines,
        and all those of the Geshurites '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '(from the Shihor, which is east of Egypt, northward to the boundary
        of Ekron, it is counted as Canaanite; there are five rulers of the Philistines,
        those of Gaza, Ashdod, Ashkelon, Gath, and Ekron), and those of the Avvim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'in the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that belongs
        to the Sidonians, to Aphek, to the boundary of the Amorites, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'and the land of the Gebalites, and all Lebanon, toward the sunrise,
        from Baal-gad below Mount Hermon to Lebo-hamath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'all the inhabitants of the hill country from Lebanon to Misrephoth-maim,
        even all the Sidonians. I myself will drive them out from before the people
        of Israel. Only allot the land to Israel for an inheritance, as I have commanded
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Inheritance East of the Jordan'
      title: The Inheritance East of the Jordan
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore divide this land for an inheritance to the nine tribes
        and half the tribe of Manasseh.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'With the other half of the tribe of Manasseh[[COMMENT(0)]] the Reubenites
        and the Gadites received their inheritance, which Moses gave them, beyond
        the Jordan eastward, as Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave them: '
      comments:
      - number: '13:8 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley of the Arnon, and
        the city that is in the middle of the valley, and all the tableland of Medeba
        as far as Dibon; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in
        Heshbon, as far as the boundary of the Ammonites; '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Gilead, and the region of the Geshurites and Maacathites, and
        all Mount Hermon, and all Bashan to Salecah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and in
        Edrei (he alone was left of the remnant of the Rephaim); these Moses had
        struck and driven out. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet the people of Israel did not drive out the Geshurites or the
        Maacathites, but Geshur and Maacath dwell in the midst of Israel to this
        day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  To the tribe of Levi alone Moses gave no inheritance. The offerings
        by fire to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God of Israel are their inheritance,
        as he said to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Moses gave an inheritance to the tribe of the people of Reuben
        according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So their territory was from Aroer, which is on the edge of the Valley
        of the Arnon, and the city that is in the middle of the valley, and all the
        tableland by Medeba; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'with Heshbon, and all its cities that are in the tableland; Dibon,
        and Bamoth-baal, and Beth-baal-meon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and Jahaz, and Kedemoth, and Mephaath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and Kiriathaim, and Sibmah, and Zereth-shahar on the hill of the
        valley, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'and Beth-peor, and the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth-jeshimoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'that is, all the cities of the tableland, and all the kingdom of
        Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses defeated with
        the leaders of Midian, Evi and Rekem and Zur and Hur and Reba, the princes
        of Sihon, who lived in the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Balaam also, the son of Beor, the one who practiced divination, was
        killed with the sword by the people of Israel among the rest of their slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And the border of the people of Reuben was the Jordan as a boundary.
        This was the inheritance of the people of Reuben, according to their clans
        with their cities and villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Moses gave an inheritance also to the tribe of Gad, to the people
        of Gad, according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and half
        the land of the Ammonites, to Aroer, which is east of Rabbah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'and from Heshbon to Ramath-mizpeh and Betonim, and from Mahanaim
        to the territory of Debir,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:26 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'and in the valley Beth-haram, Beth-nimrah, Succoth, and Zaphon, the
        rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, having the Jordan as a boundary,
        to the lower end of the Sea of Chinnereth, eastward beyond the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the people of Gad according to their clans,
        with their cities and villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And Moses gave an inheritance to the half-tribe of Manasseh. It was
        allotted to the half-tribe of the people of Manasseh according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Their region extended from Mahanaim, through all Bashan, the whole
        kingdom of Og king of Bashan, and all the towns of Jair, which are in Bashan,
        sixty cities, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'and half Gilead, and Ashtaroth, and Edrei, the cities of the kingdom
        of Og in Bashan. These were allotted to the people of Machir the son of Manasseh
        for the half of the people of Machir according to their clans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'These are the inheritances that Moses distributed in the plains of
        Moab, beyond the Jordan east of Jericho. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: But to the tribe of Levi Moses gave no inheritance; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Israel is their inheritance, just as he said to them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Inheritance West of the Jordan'
      title: The Inheritance West of the Jordan
      number: 1
      content: "  These are the inheritances that the people of Israel received in
        the land of Canaan, which Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and
        the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of the tribes of the people of Israel
        gave them to inherit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their inheritance was by lot, just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had commanded by the hand of Moses for the nine and one-half tribes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For Moses had given an inheritance to the two and one-half tribes
        beyond the Jordan, but to the Levites he gave no inheritance among them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the people of Joseph were two tribes, Manasseh and Ephraim. And
        no portion was given to the Levites in the land, but only cities to dwell
        in, with their pasturelands for their livestock and their substance. '
      comments: []
    - name: "5: Caleb\u2019s Request and Inheritance"
      title: "Caleb\u2019s Request and Inheritance"
      number: 5
      content: 'The people of Israel did as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded
        Moses; they allotted the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the people of Judah came to Joshua at Gilgal. And Caleb the
        son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him, \u201CYou know what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said to Moses the man of God in Kadesh-barnea concerning you and me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        sent me from Kadesh-barnea to spy out the land, and I brought him word again
        as it was in my heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But my brothers who went up with me made the heart of the people
        melt; yet I wholly followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Moses swore on that day, saying, \u2018Surely the land on which
        your foot has trodden shall be an inheritance for you and your children forever,
        because you have wholly followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now, behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has kept me alive,
        just as he said, these forty-five years since the time that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spoke this word to Moses, while Israel walked in the wilderness. And now,
        behold, I am this day eighty-five years old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I am still as strong today as I was in the day that Moses sent me;
        my strength now is as my strength was then, for war and for going and coming. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So now give me this hill country of which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        spoke on that day, for you heard on that day how the Anakim were there, with
        great fortified cities. It may be that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        be with me, and I shall drive them out just as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        said.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then Joshua blessed him, and he gave Hebron to Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        for an inheritance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore Hebron became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jephunneh
        the Kenizzite to this day, because he wholly followed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Now the name of Hebron formerly was Kiriath-arba.[[COMMENT(0)]] (Arba
        was the greatest man among the Anakim.) And the land had rest from war.
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: 'means Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment for Judah'
      title: The Allotment for Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  The allotment for the tribe of the people of Judah according to
        their clans reached southward to the boundary of Edom, to the wilderness
        of Zin at the farthest south. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And their south boundary ran from the end of the Salt Sea, from the
        bay that faces southward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'It goes out southward of the ascent of Akrabbim, passes along to
        Zin, and goes up south of Kadesh-barnea, along by Hezron, up to Addar, turns
        about to Karka, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'passes along to Azmon, goes out by the Brook of Egypt, and comes
        to its end at the sea. This shall be your south boundary. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the east boundary is the Salt Sea, to the mouth of the Jordan.
        And the boundary on the north side runs from the bay of the sea at the mouth
        of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the boundary goes up to Beth-hoglah and passes along north of
        Beth-arabah. And the boundary goes up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the boundary goes up to Debir from the Valley of Achor, and so
        northward, turning toward Gilgal, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim,
        which is on the south side of the valley. And the boundary passes along to
        the waters of En-shemesh and ends at En-rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the boundary goes up by the Valley of the Son of Hinnom at the
        southern shoulder of the Jebusite (that is, Jerusalem). And the boundary
        goes up to the top of the mountain that lies over against the Valley of Hinnom,
        on the west, at the northern end of the Valley of Rephaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the boundary extends from the top of the mountain to the spring
        of the waters of Nephtoah, and from there to the cities of Mount Ephron.
        Then the boundary bends around to Baalah (that is, Kiriath-jearim). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the boundary circles west of Baalah to Mount Seir, passes along
        to the northern shoulder of Mount Jearim (that is, Chesalon), and goes down
        to Beth-shemesh and passes along by Timnah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The boundary goes out to the shoulder of the hill north of Ekron,
        then the boundary bends around to Shikkeron and passes along to Mount Baalah
        and goes out to Jabneel. Then the boundary comes to an end at the sea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the west boundary was the Great Sea with its coastline. This
        is the boundary around the people of Judah according to their clans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'According to the commandment of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to
        Joshua, he gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh a portion among the people
        of Judah, Kiriath-arba, that is, Hebron (Arba was the father of Anak). '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak, Sheshai and
        Ahiman and Talmai, the descendants of Anak. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he went up from there against the inhabitants of Debir. Now the
        name of Debir formerly was Kiriath-sepher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Caleb said, \u201CWhoever strikes Kiriath-sepher and captures
        it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter as wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, captured it.
        And he gave him Achsah his daughter as wife. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field.
        And she got off her donkey, and Caleb said to her, \u201CWhat do you want?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "She said to him, \u201CGive me a blessing. Since you have given me
        the land of the Negeb, give me also springs of water.\u201D And he gave her
        the upper springs and the lower springs.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Judah according
        to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The cities belonging to the tribe of the people of Judah in the extreme
        south, toward the boundary of Edom, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Ziph, Telem, Bealoth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Hazor-hadattah, Kerioth-hezron (that is, Hazor), '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Amam, Shema, Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hazar-gaddah, Heshmon, Beth-pelet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Hazar-shual, Beersheba, Biziothiah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Baalah, Iim, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: in all, twenty-nine cities with
        their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And in the lowland, Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Zanoah, En-gannim, Tappuah, Enam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Shaaraim, Adithaim, Gederah, Gederothaim: fourteen cities with their
        villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal-gad, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Dilean, Mizpeh, Joktheel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Cabbon, Lahmam, Chitlish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Gederoth, Beth-dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteen cities with their
        villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '  Libnah, Ether, Ashan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Iphtah, Ashnah, Nezib, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: '  Ekron, with its towns and its villages; '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'from Ekron to the sea, all that were by the side of Ashdod, with
        their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '  Ashdod, its towns and its villages; Gaza, its towns and its villages;
        to the Brook of Egypt, and the Great Sea with its coastline.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'And in the hill country, Shamir, Jattir, Socoh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Dannah, Kiriath-sannah (that is, Debir), '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim, '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Goshen, Holon, and Giloh: eleven cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Arab, Dumah, Eshan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'Janim, Beth-tappuah, Aphekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Humtah, Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron), and Zior: nine cities with
        their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: '  Maon, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'Halhul, Beth-zur, Gedor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Maarath, Beth-anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: '  Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), and Rabbah: two cities
        with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'In the wilderness, Beth-arabah, Middin, Secacah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'Nibshan, the City of Salt, and Engedi: six cities with their villages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: But the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the people of Judah
        could not drive out, so the Jebusites dwell with the people of Judah at Jerusalem
        to this day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Allotment for Ephraim and Manasseh'
      title: The Allotment for Ephraim and Manasseh
      number: 1
      content: '  The allotment of the people of Joseph went from the Jordan by Jericho,
        east of the waters of Jericho, into the wilderness, going up from Jericho
        into the hill country to Bethel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then going from Bethel to Luz, it passes along to Ataroth, the territory
        of the Archites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then it goes down westward to the territory of the Japhletites, as
        far as the territory of Lower Beth-horon, then to Gezer, and it ends at the
        sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: '  The people of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, received their inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The territory of the people of Ephraim by their clans was as follows:
        the boundary of their inheritance on the east was Ataroth-addar as far as
        Upper Beth-horon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and the boundary goes from there to the sea. On the north is Michmethath.
        Then on the east the boundary turns around toward Taanath-shiloh and passes
        along beyond it on the east to Janoah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then it goes down from Janoah to Ataroth and to Naarah, and touches
        Jericho, ending at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'From Tappuah the boundary goes westward to the brook Kanah and ends
        at the sea. Such is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Ephraim
        by their clans, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'together with the towns that were set apart for the people of Ephraim
        within the inheritance of the Manassites, all those towns with their villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: However, they did not drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer,
        so the Canaanites have lived in the midst of Ephraim to this day but have
        been made to do forced labor.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Then allotment was made to the people of Manasseh, for he was the
        firstborn of Joseph. To Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead,
        were allotted Gilead and Bashan, because he was a man of war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And allotments were made to the rest of the people of Manasseh by
        their clans, Abiezer, Helek, Asriel, Shechem, Hepher, and Shemida. These
        were the male descendants of Manasseh the son of Joseph, by their clans.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now Zelophehad the son of Hepher, son of Gilead, son of Machir, son
        of Manasseh, had no sons, but only daughters, and these are the names of
        his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They approached Eleazar the priest and Joshua the son of Nun and
        the leaders and said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded Moses
        to give us an inheritance along with our brothers.\u201D So according to
        the mouth of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> he gave them an inheritance
        among the brothers of their father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Thus there fell to Manasseh ten portions, besides the land of Gilead
        and Bashan, which is on the other side of the Jordan, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance along with
        his sons. The land of Gilead was allotted to the rest of the people of Manasseh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The territory of Manasseh reached from Asher to Michmethath, which
        is east of Shechem. Then the boundary goes along southward to the inhabitants
        of En-tappuah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The land of Tappuah belonged to Manasseh, but the town of Tappuah
        on the boundary of Manasseh belonged to the people of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then the boundary went down to the brook Kanah. These cities, to
        the south of the brook, among the cities of Manasseh, belong to Ephraim.
        Then the boundary of Manasseh goes on the north side of the brook and ends
        at the sea, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "the land to the south being Ephraim\u2019s and that to the north
        being Manasseh\u2019s, with the sea forming its boundary. On the north Asher
        is reached, and on the east Issachar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Also in Issachar and in Asher Manasseh had Beth-shean and its villages,
        and Ibleam and its villages, and the inhabitants of Dor and its villages,
        and the inhabitants of En-dor and its villages, and the inhabitants of Taanach
        and its villages, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages; the third
        is Naphath.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '17:11 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew is uncertain
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yet the people of Manasseh could not take possession of those cities,
        but the Canaanites persisted in dwelling in that land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now when the people of Israel grew strong, they put the Canaanites
        to forced labor, but did not utterly drive them out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then the people of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, \u201CWhy have
        you given me but one lot and one portion as an inheritance, although I am
        a numerous people, since all along the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has blessed
        me?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Joshua said to them, \u201CIf you are a numerous people, go up
        by yourselves to the forest, and there clear ground for yourselves in the
        land of the Perizzites and the Rephaim, since the hill country of Ephraim
        is too narrow for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "The people of Joseph said, \u201CThe hill country is not enough for
        us. Yet all the Canaanites who dwell in the plain have chariots of iron,
        both those in Beth-shean and its villages and those in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Joshua said to the house of Joseph, to Ephraim and Manasseh,
        \u201CYou are a numerous people and have great power. You shall not have
        one allotment only, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "but the hill country shall be yours, for though it is a forest, you
        shall clear it and possess it to its farthest borders. For you shall drive
        out the Canaanites, though they have chariots of iron, and though they are
        strong.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Allotment of the Remaining Land'
      title: Allotment of the Remaining Land
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the whole congregation of the people of Israel assembled at
        Shiloh and set up the tent of meeting there. The land lay subdued before
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There remained among the people of Israel seven tribes whose inheritance
        had not yet been apportioned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Joshua said to the people of Israel, \u201CHow long will you put
        off going in to take possession of the land, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of your fathers, has given you? "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Provide three men from each tribe, and I will send them out that
        they may set out and go up and down the land. They shall write a description
        of it with a view to their inheritances, and then come to me. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They shall divide it into seven portions. Judah shall continue in
        his territory on the south, and the house of Joseph shall continue in their
        territory on the north. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And you shall describe the land in seven divisions and bring the
        description here to me. And I will cast lots for you here before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The Levites have no portion among you, for the priesthood of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is their heritage. And Gad and Reuben and half
        the tribe of Manasseh have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan eastward,
        which Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "So the men arose and went, and Joshua charged those who went to write
        the description of the land, saying, \u201CGo up and down in the land and
        write a description and return to me. And I will cast lots for you here before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in Shiloh.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the men went and passed up and down in the land and wrote in a
        book a description of it by towns in seven divisions. Then they came to Joshua
        to the camp at Shiloh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Inheritance for Benjamin'
      title: The Inheritance for Benjamin
      number: 10
      content: 'and Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And there Joshua apportioned the land to the people of Israel, to each his
        portion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The lot of the tribe of the people of Benjamin according to its clans
        came up, and the territory allotted to it fell between the people of Judah
        and the people of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'On the north side their boundary began at the Jordan. Then the boundary
        goes up to the shoulder north of Jericho, then up through the hill country
        westward, and it ends at the wilderness of Beth-aven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From there the boundary passes along southward in the direction of
        Luz, to the shoulder of Luz (that is, Bethel), then the boundary goes down
        to Ataroth-addar, on the mountain that lies south of Lower Beth-horon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the boundary goes in another direction, turning on the western
        side southward from the mountain that lies to the south, opposite Beth-horon,
        and it ends at Kiriath-baal (that is, Kiriath-jearim), a city belonging to
        the people of Judah. This forms the western side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the southern side begins at the outskirts of Kiriath-jearim.
        And the boundary goes from there to Ephron,[[COMMENT(0)]]  to the spring
        of the waters of Nephtoah. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:15 '
        content: 'See 15:9; Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the boundary goes down to the border of the mountain that overlooks
        the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, which is at the north end of the Valley
        of Rephaim. And it then goes down the Valley of Hinnom, south of the shoulder
        of the Jebusites, and downward to En-rogel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then it bends in a northerly direction going on to En-shemesh, and
        from there goes to Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim. Then
        it goes down to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and passing on to the north of the shoulder of Beth-arabah[[COMMENT(0)]]
        it goes down to the Arabah. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:18 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then the boundary passes on to the north of the shoulder of Beth-hoglah.
        And the boundary ends at the northern bay of the Salt Sea, at the south end
        of the Jordan: this is the southern border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The Jordan forms its boundary on the eastern side. This is the inheritance
        of the people of Benjamin, according to their clans, boundary by boundary
        all around.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now the cities of the tribe of the people of Benjamin according to
        their clans were Jericho, Beth-hoglah, Emek-keziz, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Beth-arabah, Zemaraim, Bethel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Avvim, Parah, Ophrah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Chephar-ammoni, Ophni, Geba\u2014twelve cities with their villages: "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Gibeon, Ramah, Beeroth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Mizpeh, Chephirah, Mozah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Rekem, Irpeel, Taralah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Zela, Haeleph, Jebus[[COMMENT(0)]] (that is, Jerusalem), Gibeah and
        Kiriath-jearim\u2014fourteen cities with their villages. This is the inheritance
        of the people of Benjamin according to its clans."
      comments:
      - number: '18:28 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew Hebrew Septuagint; Hebrew '
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Inheritance for Simeon'
      title: The Inheritance for Simeon
      number: 1
      content: '  The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of the people
        of Simeon, according to their clans, and their inheritance was in the midst
        of the inheritance of the people of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And they had for their inheritance Beersheba, Sheba, Moladah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Hazar-shual, Balah, Ezem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Ziklag, Beth-marcaboth, Hazar-susah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Beth-lebaoth, and Sharuhen\u2014thirteen cities with their villages; "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan\u2014four cities with their villages, "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'together with all the villages around these cities as far as Baalath-beer,
        Ramah of the Negeb. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the people of
        Simeon according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Inheritance for Zebulun'
      title: The Inheritance for Zebulun
      number: 9
      content: 'The inheritance of the people of Simeon formed part of the territory
        of the people of Judah. Because the portion of the people of Judah was too
        large for them, the people of Simeon obtained an inheritance in the midst
        of their inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The third lot came up for the people of Zebulun, according to their
        clans. And the territory of their inheritance reached as far as Sarid. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then their boundary goes up westward and on to Mareal and touches
        Dabbesheth, then the brook that is east of Jokneam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'From Sarid it goes in the other direction eastward toward the sunrise
        to the boundary of Chisloth-tabor. From there it goes to Daberath, then up
        to Japhia. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From there it passes along on the east toward the sunrise to Gath-hepher,
        to Eth-kazin, and going on to Rimmon it bends toward Neah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'then on the north the boundary turns about to Hannathon, and it ends
        at the Valley of Iphtahel; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "and Kattath, Nahalal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem\u2014twelve
        cities with their villages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The Inheritance for Issachar'
      title: The Inheritance for Issachar
      number: 16
      content: "This is the inheritance of the people of Zebulun, according to their
        clans\u2014these cities with their villages.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The fourth lot came out for Issachar, for the people of Issachar,
        according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their territory included Jezreel, Chesulloth, Shunem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Hapharaim, Shion, Anaharath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Rabbith, Kishion, Ebez, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Remeth, En-gannim, En-haddah, Beth-pazzez. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The boundary also touches Tabor, Shahazumah, and Beth-shemesh, and
        its boundary ends at the Jordan\u2014sixteen cities with their villages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: The Inheritance for Asher'
      title: The Inheritance for Asher
      number: 23
      content: "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Issachar, according
        to their clans\u2014the cities with their villages.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The fifth lot came out for the tribe of the people of Asher according
        to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Their territory included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Allammelech, Amad, and Mishal. On the west it touches Carmel and
        Shihor-libnath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'then it turns eastward, it goes to Beth-dagon, and touches Zebulun
        and the Valley of Iphtahel northward to Beth-emek and Neiel. Then it continues
        in the north to Cabul, '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, Kanah, as far as Sidon the Great. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the boundary turns to Ramah, reaching to the fortified city
        of Tyre. Then the boundary turns to Hosah, and it ends at the sea; Mahalab,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Achzib, '
      comments:
      - number: '19:29 '
        content: 'Compare Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Ummah, Aphek and Rehob\u2014twenty-two cities with their villages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: The Inheritance for Naphtali'
      title: The Inheritance for Naphtali
      number: 31
      content: "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Asher according
        to their clans\u2014these cities with their villages.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The sixth lot came out for the people of Naphtali, for the people
        of Naphtali, according to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And their boundary ran from Heleph, from the oak in Zaanannim, and
        Adami-nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum, and it ended at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then the boundary turns westward to Aznoth-tabor and goes from there
        to Hukkok, touching Zebulun at the south and Asher on the west and Judah
        on the east at the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Chinnereth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Adamah, Ramah, Hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Kedesh, Edrei, En-hazor, '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "Yiron, Migdal-el, Horem, Beth-anath, and Beth-shemesh\u2014nineteen
        cities with their villages. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: The Inheritance for Dan'
      title: The Inheritance for Dan
      number: 39
      content: "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Naphtali according
        to their clans\u2014the cities with their villages.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'The seventh lot came out for the tribe of the people of Dan, according
        to their clans. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And the territory of its inheritance included Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir-shemesh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'Shaalabbin, Aijalon, Ithlah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Elon, Timnah, Ekron, '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath, '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Jehud, Bene-berak, Gath-rimmon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'and Me-jarkon and Rakkon with the territory over against Joppa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'When the territory of the people of Dan was lost to them, the people
        of Dan went up and fought against Leshem, and after capturing it and striking
        it with the sword they took possession of it and settled in it, calling Leshem,
        Dan, after the name of Dan their ancestor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: The Inheritance for Joshua'
      title: The Inheritance for Joshua
      number: 48
      content: "This is the inheritance of the tribe of the people of Dan, according
        to their clans\u2014these cities with their villages.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'When they had finished distributing the several territories of the
        land as inheritances, the people of Israel gave an inheritance among them
        to Joshua the son of Nun. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'By command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> they gave him the city
        that he asked, Timnath-serah in the hill country of Ephraim. And he rebuilt
        the city and settled in it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "  These are the inheritances that Eleazar the priest and Joshua the
        son of Nun and the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of the tribes of the
        people of Israel distributed by lot at Shiloh before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        at the entrance of the tent of meeting. So they finished dividing the land."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Cities of Refuge'
      title: The Cities of Refuge
      number: 1
      content: '  Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Joshua, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSay to the people of Israel, \u2018Appoint the cities of refuge,
        of which I spoke to you through Moses, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'that the manslayer who strikes any person without intent or unknowingly
        may flee there. They shall be for you a refuge from the avenger of blood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He shall flee to one of these cities and shall stand at the entrance
        of the gate of the city and explain his case to the elders of that city.
        Then they shall take him into the city and give him a place, and he shall
        remain with them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not give up the
        manslayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unknowingly, and
        did not hate him in the past. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he shall remain in that city until he has stood before the congregation
        for judgment, until the death of him who is high priest at the time. Then
        the manslayer may return to his own town and his own home, to the town from
        which he fled.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So they set apart Kedesh in Galilee in the hill country of Naphtali,
        and Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim, and Kiriath-arba (that is, Hebron)
        in the hill country of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And beyond the Jordan east of Jericho, they appointed Bezer in the
        wilderness on the tableland, from the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead,
        from the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: These were the cities designated for all the people of Israel and
        for the stranger sojourning among them, that anyone who killed a person without
        intent could flee there, so that he might not die by the hand of the avenger
        of blood, till he stood before the congregation.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cities and Pasturelands Allotted to Levi'
      title: Cities and Pasturelands Allotted to Levi
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the heads of the fathers\u2019 houses of the Levites came
        to Eleazar the priest and to Joshua the son of Nun and to the heads of the
        fathers\u2019 houses of the tribes of the people of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And they said to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, \u201CThe
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded through Moses that we be given cities
        to dwell in, along with their pasturelands for our livestock.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So by command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> the people of Israel
        gave to the Levites the following cities and pasturelands out of their inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The lot came out for the clans of the Kohathites. So those Levites
        who were descendants of Aaron the priest received by lot from the tribes
        of Judah, Simeon, and Benjamin, thirteen cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the rest of the Kohathites received by lot from the clans of
        the tribe of Ephraim, from the tribe of Dan and the half-tribe of Manasseh,
        ten cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The Gershonites received by lot from the clans of the tribe of Issachar,
        from the tribe of Asher, from the tribe of Naphtali, and from the half-tribe
        of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Merarites according to their clans received from the tribe of
        Reuben, the tribe of Gad, and the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These cities and their pasturelands the people of Israel gave by
        lot to the Levites, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had commanded through
        Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Out of the tribe of the people of Judah and the tribe of the people
        of Simeon they gave the following cities mentioned by name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'which went to the descendants of Aaron, one of the clans of the Kohathites
        who belonged to the people of Levi; since the lot fell to them first. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They gave them Kiriath-arba (Arba being the father of Anak), that
        is Hebron, in the hill country of Judah, along with the pasturelands around
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But the fields of the city and its villages had been given to Caleb
        the son of Jephunneh as his possession.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And to the descendants of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron, the
        city of refuge for the manslayer, with its pasturelands, Libnah with its
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Jattir with its pasturelands, Eshtemoa with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Holon with its pasturelands, Debir with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Ain with its pasturelands, Juttah with its pasturelands, Beth-shemesh
        with its pasturelands\u2014nine cities out of these two tribes; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'then out of the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon with its pasturelands,
        Geba with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Anathoth with its pasturelands, and Almon with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The cities of the descendants of Aaron, the priests, were in all
        thirteen cities with their pasturelands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '  As to the rest of the Kohathites belonging to the Kohathite clans
        of the Levites, the cities allotted to them were out of the tribe of Ephraim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To them were given Shechem, the city of refuge for the manslayer,
        with its pasturelands in the hill country of Ephraim, Gezer with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Kibzaim with its pasturelands, Beth-horon with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Dan, Elteke with its pasturelands, Gibbethon
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Aijalon with its pasturelands, Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "and out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Taanach with its pasturelands,
        and Gath-rimmon with its pasturelands\u2014two cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The cities of the clans of the rest of the Kohathites were ten in
        all with their pasturelands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  And to the Gershonites, one of the clans of the Levites, were given
        out of the half-tribe of Manasseh, Golan in Bashan with its pasturelands,
        the city of refuge for the manslayer, and Beeshterah with its pasturelands\u2014two
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Issachar, Kishion with its pasturelands,
        Daberath with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Jarmuth with its pasturelands, En-gannim with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Asher, Mishal with its pasturelands, Abdon
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Helkath with its pasturelands, and Rehob with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "and out of the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its pasturelands,
        the city of refuge for the manslayer, Hammoth-dor with its pasturelands,
        and Kartan with its pasturelands\u2014three cities. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The cities of the several clans of the Gershonites were in all thirteen
        cities with their pasturelands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: '  And to the rest of the Levites, the Merarite clans, were given
        out of the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its pasturelands, Kartah with its
        pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "Dimnah with its pasturelands, Nahalal with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with its pasturelands, Jahaz
        with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Kedemoth with its pasturelands, and Mephaath with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with its pasturelands,
        the city of refuge for the manslayer, Mahanaim with its pasturelands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "Heshbon with its pasturelands, Jazer with its pasturelands\u2014four
        cities in all. "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'As for the cities of the several Merarite clans, that is, the remainder
        of the clans of the Levites, those allotted to them were in all twelve cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '  The cities of the Levites in the midst of the possession of the
        people of Israel were in all forty-eight cities with their pasturelands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'These cities each had its pasturelands around it. So it was with
        all these cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: '  Thus the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave to Israel all the land
        that he swore to give to their fathers. And they took possession of it, and
        they settled there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave them rest on every side
        just as he had sworn to their fathers. Not one of all their enemies had withstood
        them, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had given all their enemies into
        their hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: Not one word of all the good promises that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had made to the house of Israel had failed; all came to pass.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Eastern Tribes Return Home'
      title: The Eastern Tribes Return Home
      number: 1
      content: '  At that time Joshua summoned the Reubenites and the Gadites and
        the half-tribe of Manasseh, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said to them, \u201CYou have kept all that Moses the servant
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded you and have obeyed my voice
        in all that I have commanded you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You have not forsaken your brothers these many days, down to this
        day, but have been careful to keep the charge of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given rest to
        your brothers, as he promised them. Therefore turn and go to your tents in
        the land where your possession lies, which Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        gave you on the other side of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Only be very careful to observe the commandment and the law that
        Moses the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> commanded you, to love
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and to walk in all his ways and
        to keep his commandments and to cling to him and to serve him with all your
        heart and with all your soul.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their
        tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now to the one half of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession
        in Bashan, but to the other half Joshua had given a possession beside their
        brothers in the land west of the Jordan. And when Joshua sent them away to
        their homes and blessed them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "he said to them, \u201CGo back to your tents with much wealth and
        with very much livestock, with silver, gold, bronze, and iron, and with much
        clothing. Divide the spoil of your enemies with your brothers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "9: The Eastern Tribes\u2019 Altar of Witness"
      title: "The Eastern Tribes\u2019 Altar of Witness"
      number: 9
      content: 'So the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh returned home, parting from the people of Israel at Shiloh, which
        is in the land of Canaan, to go to the land of Gilead, their own land of
        which they had possessed themselves by command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        through Moses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when they came to the region of the Jordan that is in the land
        of Canaan, the people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh built there an altar by the Jordan, an altar of imposing size. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the people of Israel heard it said, \u201CBehold, the people
        of Reuben and the people of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh have built
        the altar at the frontier of the land of Canaan, in the region about the
        Jordan, on the side that belongs to the people of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And when the people of Israel heard of it, the whole assembly of
        the people of Israel gathered at Shiloh to make war against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the people of Israel sent to the people of Reuben and the people
        of Gad and the half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, Phinehas the
        son of Eleazar the priest, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'and with him ten chiefs, one from each of the tribal families of
        Israel, every one of them the head of a family among the clans of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they came to the people of Reuben, the people of Gad, and the
        half-tribe of Manasseh, in the land of Gilead, and they said to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CThus says the whole congregation of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018What is this breach of faith that you have committed against the God
        of Israel in turning away this day from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        by building yourselves an altar this day in rebellion against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>? "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Have we not had enough of the sin at Peor from which even yet we
        have not cleansed ourselves, and for which there came a plague upon the congregation
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'that you too must turn away this day from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?
        And if you too rebel against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> today then tomorrow
        he will be angry with the whole congregation of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But now, if the land of your possession is unclean, pass over into
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s land where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        tabernacle stands, and take for yourselves a possession among us. Only do
        not rebel against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> or make us as rebels by
        building for yourselves an altar other than the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Did not Achan the son of Zerah break faith in the matter of the devoted
        things, and wrath fell upon all the congregation of Israel? And he did not
        perish alone for his iniquity.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the people of Reuben, the people of Gad, and the half-tribe
        of Manasseh said in answer to the heads of the families of Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThe Mighty One, God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! The Mighty
        One, God, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>! He knows; and let Israel itself
        know! If it was in rebellion or in breach of faith against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        do not spare us today "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'for building an altar to turn away from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Or if we did so to offer burnt offerings or grain offerings or peace offerings
        on it, may the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> himself take vengeance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "No, but we did it from fear that in time to come your children might
        say to our children, \u2018What have you to do with the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has made the Jordan a boundary
        between us and you, you people of Reuben and people of Gad. You have no portion
        in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019 So your children might make our
        children cease to worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Therefore we said, \u2018Let us now build an altar, not for burnt
        offering, nor for sacrifice, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "but to be a witness between us and you, and between our generations
        after us, that we do perform the service of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in his presence with our burnt offerings and sacrifices and peace offerings,
        so your children will not say to our children in time to come, \u201CYou
        have no portion in the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And we thought, \u2018If this should be said to us or to our descendants
        in time to come, we should say, \u201CBehold, the copy of the altar of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which our fathers made, not for burnt offerings,
        nor for sacrifice, but to be a witness between us and you.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "Far be it from us that we should rebel against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and turn away this day from following the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  by
        building an altar for burnt offering, grain offering, or sacrifice, other
        than the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God that stands before
        his tabernacle!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'When Phinehas the priest and the chiefs of the congregation, the
        heads of the families of Israel who were with him, heard the words that the
        people of Reuben and the people of Gad and the people of Manasseh spoke,
        it was good in their eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said to the people of
        Reuben and the people of Gad and the people of Manasseh, \u201CToday we know
        that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is in our midst, because you have not
        committed this breach of faith against the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. Now
        you have delivered the people of Israel from the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Then Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, and the chiefs, returned
        from the people of Reuben and the people of Gad in the land of Gilead to
        the land of Canaan, to the people of Israel, and brought back word to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And the report was good in the eyes of the people of Israel. And
        the people of Israel blessed God and spoke no more of making war against
        them to destroy the land where the people of Reuben and the people of Gad
        were settled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "The people of Reuben and the people of Gad called the altar Witness,
        \u201CFor,\u201D they said, \u201Cit is a witness between us that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Joshua\u2019s Charge to Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Charge to Israel\u2019s Leaders"
      number: 1
      content: '  A long time afterward, when the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had
        given rest to Israel from all their surrounding enemies, and Joshua was old
        and well advanced in years, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Joshua summoned all Israel, its elders and heads, its judges and
        officers, and said to them, \u201CI am now old and well advanced in years. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And you have seen all that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God
        has done to all these nations for your sake, for it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God who has fought for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Behold, I have allotted to you as an inheritance for your tribes
        those nations that remain, along with all the nations that I have already
        cut off, from the Jordan to the Great Sea in the west. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will push them back before
        you and drive them out of your sight. And you shall possess their land, just
        as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, be very strong to keep and to do all that is written in
        the Book of the Law of Moses, turning aside from it neither to the right
        hand nor to the left, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'that you may not mix with these nations remaining among you or make
        mention of the names of their gods or swear by them or serve them or bow
        down to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'but you shall cling to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God just
        as you have done to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has driven out before you great
        and strong nations. And as for you, no man has been able to stand before
        you to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'One man of you puts to flight a thousand, since it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God who fights for you, just as he promised you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Be very careful, therefore, to love the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For if you turn back and cling to the remnant of these nations remaining
        among you and make marriages with them, so that you associate with them and
        they with you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'know for certain that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God will
        no longer drive out these nations before you, but they shall be a snare and
        a trap for you, a whip on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until you perish
        from off this good ground that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has
        given you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CAnd now I am about to go the way of all the earth, and you
        know in your hearts and souls, all of you, that not one word has failed of
        all the good things[[COMMENT(0)]] that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your
        God promised concerning you. All have come to pass for you; not one of them
        has failed. "
      comments:
      - number: '23:14 '
        content: Or ; also twice in verse 15
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But just as all the good things that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God promised concerning you have been fulfilled for you, so the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will bring upon you all the evil things, until he has destroyed you from
        off this good land that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God has given
        you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "if you transgress the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        your God, which he commanded you, and go and serve other gods and bow down
        to them. Then the anger of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will be kindled
        against you, and you shall perish quickly from off the good land that he
        has given to you.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Covenant Renewal at Shechem'
      title: The Covenant Renewal at Shechem
      number: 1
      content: '  Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem and summoned
        the elders, the heads, the judges, and the officers of Israel. And they presented
        themselves before God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, \u2018Long ago, your fathers lived beyond the Euphrates,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Terah, the father of Abraham and of Nahor; and they served other gods. "
      comments:
      - number: '24:2 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then I took your father Abraham from beyond the River[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and led him through all the land of Canaan, and made his offspring many.
        I gave him Isaac. '
      comments:
      - number: '24:3 '
        content: That is, the Euphrates; also verses 14, 15
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And to Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau. And I gave Esau the hill country
        of Seir to possess, but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt with what I did in
        the midst of it, and afterward I brought you out.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201C\u2018Then I brought your fathers out of Egypt, and you came
        to the sea. And the Egyptians pursued your fathers with chariots and horsemen
        to the Red Sea. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And when they cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, he put darkness
        between you and the Egyptians and made the sea come upon them and cover them;
        and your eyes saw what I did in Egypt. And you lived in the wilderness a
        long time. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then I brought you to the land of the Amorites, who lived on the
        other side of the Jordan. They fought with you, and I gave them into your
        hand, and you took possession of their land, and I destroyed them before
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, arose and fought against
        Israel. And he sent and invited Balaam the son of Beor to curse you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'but I would not listen to Balaam. Indeed, he blessed you. So I delivered
        you out of his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And you went over the Jordan and came to Jericho, and the leaders
        of Jericho fought against you, and also the Amorites, the Perizzites, the
        Canaanites, the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites.
        And I gave them into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I sent the hornet before you, which drove them out before you,
        the two kings of the Amorites; it was not by your sword or by your bow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Choose Whom You Will Serve'
      title: Choose Whom You Will Serve
      number: 13
      content: "I gave you a land on which you had not labored and cities that you
        had not built, and you dwell in them. You eat the fruit of vineyards and
        olive orchards that you did not plant.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "  \u201CNow therefore fear the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and serve
        him in sincerity and in faithfulness. Put away the gods that your fathers
        served beyond the River and in Egypt, and serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And if it is evil in your eyes to serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        choose this day whom you will serve, whether the gods your fathers served
        in the region beyond the River, or the gods of the Amorites in whose land
        you dwell. But as for me and my house, we will serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then the people answered, \u201CFar be it from us that we should
        forsake the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to serve other gods, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'for it is the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God who brought us
        and our fathers up from the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery, and
        who did those great signs in our sight and preserved us in all the way that
        we went, and among all the peoples through whom we passed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> drove out before us all the peoples,
        the Amorites who lived in the land. Therefore we also will serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        for he is our God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "But Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou are not able to serve the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for he is a holy God. He is a jealous God; he
        will not forgive your transgressions or your sins. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "If you forsake the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and serve foreign
        gods, then he will turn and do you harm and consume you, after having done
        you good.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CNo, but we will serve the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Joshua said to the people, \u201CYou are witnesses against yourselves
        that you have chosen the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, to serve him.\u201D
        And they said, \u201CWe are witnesses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "He said, \u201CThen put away the foreign gods that are among you,
        and incline your heart to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the people said to Joshua, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God we will serve, and his voice we will obey.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and put in place
        statutes and rules for them at Shechem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And Joshua wrote these words in the Book of the Law of God. And he
        took a large stone and set it up there under the terebinth that was by the
        sanctuary of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And Joshua said to all the people, \u201CBehold, this stone shall
        be a witness against us, for it has heard all the words of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that he spoke to us. Therefore it shall be a witness against you, lest you
        deal falsely with your God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "28: Joshua\u2019s Death and Burial"
      title: "Joshua\u2019s Death and Burial"
      number: 28
      content: 'So Joshua sent the people away, every man to his inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  After these things Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        died, being 110 years old. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And they buried him in his own inheritance at Timnath-serah, which
        is in the hill country of Ephraim, north of the mountain of Gaash.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: '  Israel served the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all the days of Joshua,
        and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua and had known all the
        work that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> did for Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '  As for the bones of Joseph, which the people of Israel brought
        up from Egypt, they buried them at Shechem, in the piece of land that Jacob
        bought from the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for a hundred pieces
        of money.[[COMMENT(0)]] It became an inheritance of the descendants of Joseph.  '
      comments:
      - number: '24:32 '
        content: Hebrew ; a unit of money of unknown value
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: And Eleazar the son of Aaron died, and they buried him at Gibeah,
        the town of Phinehas his son, which had been given him in the hill country
        of Ephraim.
      comments: []
